{"type":"message","id":"8205b6af","parentId":"af8eae23","timestamp":"2026-04-06T07:40:08.935Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to find voltage classes within a substation named \"Sub-2\". I need to use the `scada-object-explore` skill for this.\n\nBased on the `SKILL.md` for `scada-object-explore`, I need to specify:\n- `folder`: The path to the substation. I will try to infer this from \"Sub-2\".\n- `pattern`: The pattern for voltage classes. From `MEMORY.md`, I know this is likely `/root/FP/prototypes/voltage class/fields`.\n- `select`: I should select relevant fields to identify the voltage classes. `title` is often used for the voltage value in Ecomet for voltage classes, and `.fp_path` is always useful.\n\nI will construct the `folder` path by assuming a common project structure, like `/root/FP/PROJECT/.../Sub-2/`. Since I don't have a specific project path, I will use a general search with `searchText` and `pattern` to find voltage classes associated with \"Sub-2\".\n\nLet's try to locate the substation first. I will use `scada-object-explore` with `searchText` \"Sub-2\" and a `pattern` that includes substation prototypes. However, I don't have a specific pattern for \"substation\" in my memory, but I know `.fp_path` contains the substation name.\n\nI will directly search for voltage classes where their path contains \"Sub-2\". This is a more direct approach since voltage levels are typically children of substations in the `.fp_path` hierarchy.\n\n**Plan:**\n1. Call `skill_run` with `scada-object-explore`.\n2. Set `pattern` to `/root/FP/prototypes/voltage class/fields`.\n3. Use `searchText` with \"Sub-2\" to find paths containing this name.\n4. Set `select` to `[\".name\", \"title\", \".fp_path\"]` to get the voltage class name, its title (which often contains the voltage value), and its full path.\n5. Set `searchIn` to `[\".fp_path\"]` to ensure the search is performed on the object's full path.\n\nLet's try to refine the search. Instead of `searchText`, I can use `fields` with a `like` operator on `.fp_path`. However, the `scada-object-explore` skill parameters documentation shows `searchText` as an option for general text search. Given the user asked for \"Sub-2 name\", `searchText` on `.fp_path` seems appropriate to find all voltage classes whose full path includes \"Sub-2\".\n\nI'll assume that \"Sub-2\" is part of the `.fp_path` of the voltage class objects.\n\n**Revised Plan:**\n1. Call `skill_run` with `scada-object-explore`.\n2. `pattern`: `/root/FP/prototypes/voltage class/fields` (from `MEMORY.md`).\n3. `searchText`: \"Sub-2\"\n4. `searchIn`: `[\".fp_path\"]`\n5. `select`: `[\".name\", \"title\", \".fp_path\"]`"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"skill_run_1775461208932_2","name":"skill_run","arguments":{"skill":"scada-object-explore","params":{"select":[".name","title",".fp_path"],"searchIn":[".fp_path"],"pattern":"/root/FP/prototypes/voltage class/fields","searchText":"Sub-2"}}}],"api":"google-generative-ai","provider":"google","model":"gemini-2.5-flash","usage":{"input":29624,"output":770,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30394,"cost":{"input":0.0088872,"output":0.001925,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0108122}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775461204192,"responseId":"VWPTafI-_-mR1Q-akepY"}}
